{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01GC6bXBzgx7h5KarcNqPkFp","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the structure. The 3-way match formula checks: company, account, and xchar between Sheet4 and CBtrans.\n\nSheet4 columns: B=Company, I=account, E=xchar\nCBtrans columns: A=company, H=account, K=xchar\n\nFor each row in Sheet4, I need to check if there's a matching row in CBtrans where all three match (company, account, xchar). If yes → \"Match\", if no → \"-\".\n\nLet me check:\n- Row 2: company=5180, account='Sam', xchar=-6408.95 → CBtrans row 2: company=5180, account='Sam', xchar=-6408.95 → Match\n\n\n- Row 3: company=5176, account='Derek', xchar=-6404.61 → CBtrans row 3 has 'John' instead of 'Derek', so no match\n- Row 4: company=5278, account='Paul', xchar=-5654.35 → CBtrans row 4 has 'Martyn' instead of 'Paul', so I need to search through all CBtrans rows to find a match\n- Row 5: company=5323, account='Mark', xchar=-5212.59 → checking this row now\n\nRows 5, 6, and 7 all match their corresponding CBtrans rows. But I should write a proper script to handle the full 3-way matching across all the data instead of doing this manually, since there could be more rows and the existing values in K2 and K3 suggest there's already a pattern established.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":7882,"cache_read_input_tokens":13878,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":7882},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e33dd6b3-957b-4081-ac8a-d162283c5d38","uuid":"b518604f-835e-422e-b37d-3858470407a2"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01GC6bXBzgx7h5KarcNqPkFp","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01EAcsoyYgdBdJywg3xfR6RG","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"python3 -c \"\nimport openpyxl\nfrom openpyxl.styles import PatternFill\nfrom copy import copy\n\nwb = openpyxl.load_workbook('input.xlsx')\nws4 = wb['Sheet4']\ncb = wb['CBtrans']\n\n# Build lookup set from CBtrans: (company, account, xchar)\nlookup = set()\nfor row in cb.iter_rows(min_row=2, max_row=cb.max_row, values_only=True):\n    company, account, xchar = row[0], row[7], row[10]\n    # strip strings\n    if isinstance(account, str):\n        account = account.strip()\n    lookup.add((company, account, xchar))\n\nprint(f'CBtrans lookup entries: {len(lookup)}')\n\nfill = PatternFill(start_color='FF66CC', end_color='FF66CC', fill_type='solid')\n\nfor r in range(2, 8):\n    company = ws4.cell(r, 2).value  # B\n    account = ws4.cell(r, 9).value  # I\n    xchar = ws4.cell(r, 5).value    # E\n    if isinstance(account, str):\n        account = account.strip()\n    \n    matched = (company, account, xchar) in lookup\n    result = 'Match' if matched else '-'\n    cell = ws4.cell(r, 11)\n    cell.value = result\n    cell.fill = fill\n    print(f'Row {r}: company={company}, account={account}, xchar={xchar} -> {result}')\n\nwb.save('output.xlsx')\nprint('Done')\n\"\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":7882,"cache_read_input_tokens":13878,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":7882},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e33dd6b3-957b-4081-ac8a-d162283c5d38","uuid":"ec005fa1-0d53-426d-be6c-4e1e0d32a5b5"}
